{"title_page": "Electoral district of Whitsunday", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox Australian Electorate |name     = Whitsunday\n|federal=|state    = qld\n|upper=|image    = ECQ-2017-Final-Whitsunday.pdf\n|caption  = Electoral map of Whitsunday 2017\n|lifespan =\n|mp       = [[Jason Costigan]]\n|mp-party = [[North Queensland First]]\n|namesake = [[Whitsunday Island]]\n|electors = 32156\n|electors_year = 2015\n|area     = 27761\n|class    =\n|coordinates = {{coord|20|35|S|149|2|E|type:adm2nd|display=inline,title}}\n| near-n             = ''[[Coral Sea]]''\n| near-ne            = ''[[Coral Sea]]''\n| near-e             = ''[[Coral Sea]]''\n| near-se            = [[Electoral district of Mackay|Mackay]]\n| near-s             = [[Electoral district of Mirani|Mirani]]\n| near-sw            = [[Electoral district of Mirani|Mirani]]\n| near-w             = [[Electoral district of Burdekin|Burdekin]]\n| near-nw            = [[Electoral district of Burdekin|Burdekin]]\n}}\n[[File:QLD - Whitsunday 2008.png|thumb|Electoral map of Whitsunday 2008]]\n'''Whitsunday''' is an electoral division in the [[Legislative Assembly of Queensland]], [[Queensland]], Australia.\n\nIt extends from the northern suburbs of [[Mackay, Queensland|Mackay]] to [[Bowen, Queensland|Bowen]] and [[Proserpine, Queensland|Proserpine]] as well as east to the [[Whitsunday Islands]].\n\n==Members for Whitsunday==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!\n!Member\n!Party affiliation\n!Period\n|-\n| {{Australian party style|Nationals QLD}}|&nbsp;\n| [[Lloyd Roberts (politician)|Lloyd Roberts]]\n| [[National Party of Australia \u2013 Queensland|Country Party]]\n| 1950\u20131961\n|-\n| {{Australian party style|Nationals QLD}}|&nbsp;\n|rowspan=\"2\"| [[Ron Camm]]\n| [[National Party of Australia \u2013 Queensland|Country]]\n| 1961\u20131974\n|-\n| {{Australian party style|Nationals QLD}}|&nbsp;\n| [[National Party of Australia \u2013 Queensland|National]]\n| 1974\u20131980\n|-\n| {{Australian party style|Nationals QLD}}|&nbsp;\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Geoff Muntz]]\n| [[National Party of Australia \u2013 Queensland|National]]\n| 1980\u20131989\n|-\n| {{Australian party style|Independent}}|&nbsp;\n| [[Independent (politician)|Independent]]\n| 1989\n|-\n| {{Australian party style|Labor}}|&nbsp;\n| [[Lorraine Bird]]\n| [[Australian Labor Party (Queensland Branch)|Labor]]\n| 1989\u20131998\n|-\n| {{Australian party style|One Nation}}|&nbsp;\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Harry Black (politician)|Harry Black]]\n| [[One Nation Party|One Nation]]\n| 1998\u20131999\n|-\n| {{Australian party style|City Country Alliance}}|&nbsp;\n| [[City Country Alliance]]\n| 1999\u20132001\n|-\n| {{Australian party style|Labor}}|&nbsp;\n| [[Jan Jarratt]]\n| [[Australian Labor Party (Queensland Branch)|Labor]]\n| 2001\u20132012\n|-\n| {{Australian party style|Liberal National}}|&nbsp;\n| rowspan=\"3\"|[[Jason Costigan]]\n| [[Liberal National Party of Queensland|Liberal National]]\n| 2012\u20132019\n|-\n| {{Australian party style|Independent}}|&nbsp;\n| [[Independent politician|Independent]]\n| 2019\n|-\n| {{Australian party style|North Queensland}}|&nbsp;\n| [[North Queensland First]]\n| 2019\u2013present\n|}\n\n==Election results==\n{{main|Electoral results for the district of Whitsunday}}\n\n{{Election box begin\n|title=[[2017 Queensland state election]]: Whitsunday<ref>[https://results.ecq.qld.gov.au/elections/state/State2017/results/district92.html 2017 State General Election - Whitsunday - District Summary], ECQ.</ref>\n}}\n{{Election box candidate AU party\n|candidate = [[Jason Costigan]]\n|party = Liberal National\n|votes = 8,774\n|percentage = 32.2\n|change = \u22129.5\n}}\n{{Election box candidate AU party\n|candidate = Bronwyn Taha\n|party = Labor QLD\n|votes = 8,503\n|percentage = 31.2\n|change = \u22124.7\n}}\n{{Election box candidate AU party\n|candidate = Noel Skippen\n|party = One Nation\n|votes = 5,471\n|percentage = 20.1\n|change = +20.1\n}}\n{{Election box candidate AU party\n|candidate = Jenny Whitney\n|party = Katter's Australian Party\n|votes = 2,499\n|percentage = 9.2\n|change = +9.2\n}}\n{{Election box candidate AU party\n|candidate = Imogen Lindenberg\n|party = Greens QLD\n|votes = 1,562\n|percentage = 5.7\n|change = \u22120.9\n}}\n{{Election box candidate AU party\n|candidate = Dan Van Blarcom\n|party = Independent\n|votes = 477\n|percentage = 1.7\n|change = +1.7\n}}\n{{Election box formal\n|votes = 27,286\n|percentage = 96.0\n|change = \u22121.9\n}}\n{{Election box informal\n|votes = 1,147\n|percentage = 4.0\n|change = +1.9\n}}\n{{Election box turnout\n|votes = 28,433\n|percentage = 86.3\n|change = \u22120.1\n}}\n{{Election box 2pp}}\n{{Election box candidate AU party|\n|candidate = [[Jason Costigan]]\n|party = Liberal National\n|votes = 13,829\n|percentage = 50.7\n|change = +0.1\n}}\n{{Election box candidate AU party|\n|candidate = Bronwyn Taha\n|party = Labor QLD\n|votes = 13,457\n|percentage = 49.3\n|change = \u22120.1\n}}\n{{Election box hold AU party|\n|winner = Liberal National\n|swing = +0.1\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.abc.net.au/elections/qld/2009/guide/whit.htm|title=Electorate Profile|last=Green|first=Antony|author-link=Antony Green|publisher=[[Australian Broadcasting Corporation]]}}\n\n{{Electoral districts of Queensland}}\n\n[[Category:Electoral districts of Queensland|Whitsunday]]\n[[Category:Constituencies established in 1950]]\n[[Category:1950 establishments in Australia]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox Australian Electorate |name     = Whitsunday\n|federal=|state    = qld\n|upper=|image    = ECQ-2017-Final-Whitsunday.pdf\n|caption  = Electoral map of Whitsunday 2017\n|lifespan =\n|mp       = [[Jason Costigan]]\n|mp-party = [[North Queensland First]]\n|namesake = [[Whitsunday Island]]\n|electors = 32156\n|electors_year = 2015\n|area     = 27761\n|class    =\n|coordinates = {{coord|20|35|S|149|2|E|type:adm2nd|display=inline,title}}\n| near-n             = ''[[Coral Sea]]''\n| near-ne            = ''[[Coral Sea]]''\n| near-e             = ''[[Coral Sea]]''\n| near-se            = [[Electoral district of Mackay|Mackay]]\n| near-s             = [[Electoral district of Mirani|Mirani]]\n| near-sw            = [[Electoral district of Mirani|Mirani]]\n| near-w             = [[Electoral district of Burdekin|Burdekin]]\n| near-nw            = [[Electoral district of Burdekin|Burdekin]]\n}}\n[[File:QLD - Whitsunday 2008.png|thumb|Electoral map of Whitsunday 2008]]\n'''Whitsunday''' is an electoral division in the [[Legislative Assembly of Queensland]], [[Queensland]], Australia.\n\nIt extends from the northern suburbs of [[Mackay, Queensland|Mackay]] to [[Bowen, Queensland|Bowen]] and [[Proserpine, Queensland|Proserpine]] as well as east to the [[Whitsunday Islands]].\n\n==Members for Whitsunday==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!\n!Member\n!Party affiliation\n!Period\n|-\n| {{Australian party style|Nationals QLD}}|&nbsp;\n| [[Lloyd Roberts (politician)|Lloyd Roberts]]\n| [[National Party of Australia \u2013 Queensland|Country Party]]\n| 1950\u20131961\n|-\n| {{Australian party style|Nationals QLD}}|&nbsp;\n|rowspan=\"2\"| [[Ron Camm]]\n| [[National Party of Australia \u2013 Queensland|Country]]\n| 1961\u20131974\n|-\n| {{Australian party style|Nationals QLD}}|&nbsp;\n| [[National Party of Australia \u2013 Queensland|National]]\n| 1974\u20131980\n|-\n| {{Australian party style|Nationals QLD}}|&nbsp;\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Geoff Muntz]]\n| [[National Party of Australia \u2013 Queensland|National]]\n| 1980\u20131989\n|-\n| {{Australian party style|Independent}}|&nbsp;\n| [[Independent (politician)|Independent]]\n| 1989\n|-\n| {{Australian party style|Labor}}|&nbsp;\n| [[Lorraine Bird]]\n| [[Australian Labor Party (Queensland Branch)|Labor]]\n| 1989\u20131998\n|-\n| {{Australian party style|One Nation}}|&nbsp;\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Harry Black (politician)|Harry Black]]\n| [[One Nation Party|One Nation]]\n| 1998\u20131999\n|-\n| {{Australian party style|City Country Alliance}}|&nbsp;\n| [[City Country Alliance]]\n| 1999\u20132001\n|-\n| {{Australian party style|Labor}}|&nbsp;\n| [[Jan Jarratt]]\n| [[Australian Labor Party (Queensland Branch)|Labor]]\n| 2001\u20132012\n|-\n| {{Australian party style|Liberal National}}|&nbsp;\n| rowspan=\"3\"|[[Jason Costigan]]\n| [[Liberal National Party of Queensland|Liberal National]]\n| 2012\u20132019\n|-\n| {{Australian party style|Independent}}|&nbsp;\n| [[Independent politician|Independent]]\n| 2019\n|-\n| {{Australian party style|Liberal National}}|&nbsp;\n| [[North Queensland First]]\n| 2019\u2013present\n|}\n\n==Election results==\n{{main|Electoral results for the district of Whitsunday}}\n\n{{Election box begin\n|title=[[2017 Queensland state election]]: Whitsunday<ref>[https://results.ecq.qld.gov.au/elections/state/State2017/results/district92.html 2017 State General Election - Whitsunday - District Summary], ECQ.</ref>\n}}\n{{Election box candidate AU party\n|candidate = [[Jason Costigan]]\n|party = Liberal National\n|votes = 8,774\n|percentage = 32.2\n|change = \u22129.5\n}}\n{{Election box candidate AU party\n|candidate = Bronwyn Taha\n|party = Labor QLD\n|votes = 8,503\n|percentage = 31.2\n|change = \u22124.7\n}}\n{{Election box candidate AU party\n|candidate = Noel Skippen\n|party = One Nation\n|votes = 5,471\n|percentage = 20.1\n|change = +20.1\n}}\n{{Election box candidate AU party\n|candidate = Jenny Whitney\n|party = Katter's Australian Party\n|votes = 2,499\n|percentage = 9.2\n|change = +9.2\n}}\n{{Election box candidate AU party\n|candidate = Imogen Lindenberg\n|party = Greens QLD\n|votes = 1,562\n|percentage = 5.7\n|change = \u22120.9\n}}\n{{Election box candidate AU party\n|candidate = Dan Van Blarcom\n|party = Independent\n|votes = 477\n|percentage = 1.7\n|change = +1.7\n}}\n{{Election box formal\n|votes = 27,286\n|percentage = 96.0\n|change = \u22121.9\n}}\n{{Election box informal\n|votes = 1,147\n|p