{"title_page": "Yeri (singer)", "text_new": "{{short description|South Korean singer}}\n{{Korean name |Kim}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Yeri(\uc608\ub9ac)\n| image              = Kim Yeri at Asia Artist Awards on November 26, 2019.jpg\n| image_size         = \n| caption            = Yeri in November 2019\n| native_name        = \uae40\uc608\ub9bc\n| birth_name         = Kim Ye-rim\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1999|3|5}}\n| birth_place        = [[Seoul]], South Korea<ref name=smprofile>{{cite web|url=http://redvelvet.smtown.com/profile|title=Red Velvet Profile|accessdate=October 11, 2014|language=ko}}</ref>\n| alias              = Yeri\n| occupation         = Singer\n| signature          =\n| signature_size     =\n| signature_alt      = \n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| background = solo_singer\n| genre = [[K-pop]]\n| instrument = Vocals\n| years_active = 2015\u2013present\n| label = [[SM Entertainment|SM]]\n| associated_acts = {{hlist|[[Red Velvet (group)|Red Velvet]]|[[SM Rookies]]|[[SM Town]]}}\n}}\n}}\n{{Infobox Korean name\n|title = [[Korean name]]\n|hangul = {{linktext|\uae40|\uc608|\ub9bc}}\n|hanja = {{linktext|\u91d1|\u85dd|\u7433}}\n|rr = Gim Ye-rim\n|mr = Kim Yerim\n| hangulstage = {{linktext|\uc608\ub9ac}}\n| rrstage = Ye-ri\n| mrstage = Yeri\n}}\n\n'''Kim Ye-rim''' (born March 5, 1999), known by her stage name '''Yeri''', is a South Korean singer. She is a member of South Korean girl group [[Red Velvet (group)|Red Velvet]].\n\n==Early life==\nKim Ye-rim was born on March 5, 1999, in Seoul, South Korea. She has three younger sisters, Yoo-rim, Ye-eun and Chae-eun.<ref>{{cite news |title=[Why \u4eba] \ub808\ub4dc\ubca8\ubcb3 \uc608\ub9ac, \uac13 \uc2a4\ubb34\uc0b4 \ub41c \ub9c9\ub0b4\uc758 \uc644\uc131\ud615 \ubbf8\ubaa8 |url=http://www.mbcsportsplus.com/news/?mode=view&cate=general&b_idx=99908187.000#07D0 |accessdate=January 13, 2019 |work=www.xportsnews.com |date=March 6, 2018 |language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite AV media notes|title=Ice Cream Cake (Thanks To)|others=[[Red Velvet (group)|Red Velvet]]|year=2015|type=booklet|publisher=[[SM Entertainment]]|id=|language=ko}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n===Pre-debut===\nYeri joined [[SM Entertainment]] after auditioning at the SM Weekly Audition in 2011.<ref>{{cite web |title=SM \ud1a0\uc694 \uacf5\uac1c\uc624\ub514\uc158\uc73c\ub85c \ub370\ubdd4\ud55c 7\uc778 |url=https://www.dispatch.co.kr/2006376 |publisher=Dispatch |accessdate=18 February 2019 |language=ko-KR |date=15 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=SM Weekly Audition |url=https://www.smtown.com/audition/sm?lang=en |website=www.smtown.com |accessdate=18 February 2019}}</ref> In 2014, she performed as one of the upcoming members of SM Entertainment's pre-debut training group [[SM Rookies]] on [[SM Town Live World Tour IV]].<ref>{{cite news |title=\ub808\ub4dc\ubca8\ubcb3 \uc0c8 \uba64\ubc84, \uc608\ub9ac\ub294 \ub204\uad6c? 'SM\ub8e8\ud0a4\uc988 \ucd9c\uc2e0' |url=http://www.xportsnews.com/jenter/?ac=article_view&entry_id=561501 |accessdate=January 12, 2019 |work=www.xportsnews.com |date=March 11, 2015 |language=ko}}</ref> She had a brief appearance in the introduction of [[Red Velvet (group)|Red Velvet]]'s debut song, \"Happiness\", before debuting as a member.<ref name=\"happiness\">{{cite news|first=Robert|last=Kuang|title=Hidden Red Velvet Members Uncovered In 'Happiness' Music Video, Including Yeri?|url=http://www.kpopstarz.com/articles/182715/20150311/hidden-red-velvet-members.htm|accessdate=January 9, 2019|publisher=KpopStarz|date=March 11, 2015}}</ref>\n\n===2015\u2013present: Red Velvet and solo activities===\n{{see also|Red Velvet (group)}}\nYeri was introduced as a new member of Red Velvet on March 10, 2015, during the promotions of their first [[extended play]] ''[[Ice Cream Cake (EP)|Ice Cream Cake]]''.<ref name=\"rvnewmember2\">{{cite news|url=http://www.bntnews.co.uk/app/news.php?nid=18877|title=Red Velvet Makes Its Comeback With A New Member|date=March 11, 2015|work=BNT News|last1=Ahn|first1=Woorim|accessdate=January 12, 2019}}</ref> From May 9, 2015 to November 14, 2015, Yeri hosted [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]]'s music program ''[[Show! Music Core]]'', together with [[Choi Min-ho (entertainer)|Minho]] from [[Shinee]] and [[N (singer)|N]] from [[VIXX]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://v.entertain.media.daum.net/v/20150504155917581?preview=false&entertainSectionName=culture&entertainLeafName=newsview|title=[\ub2e8\ub3c5] \ub808\ub4dc\ubca8\ubcb3 \uc608\ub9ac '\uc74c\uc545\uc911\uc2ec' MC \ud655\uc815, \ub300\uc138 \uac78\uadf8\ub8f9\ub2e4\uc6b4 \ud589\ubcf4|language=ko|date=May 4, 2015|publisher=entertain.media.daum.net|accessdate=January 12, 2019}}</ref> In July 2016, Yeri was the female lead in the music video for [[J-Min]] and Shim Eun-jee's \"Way Back Home\", which was released as part of the single project ''[[SM Station]]''.<ref name=\"wbh\">{{cite news|url=http://d.kbs.co.kr/news/view.do?ncd=3307837|title=J-Min\u00b7\uc2ec\uc740\uc9c0, '\uc9d1 \uc55e\uc5d0\uc11c' \uacf5\uac1c\u2026\uc608\ub9ac MV \ucd9c\uc5f0|language=ko|date=July 7, 2016|publisher=kbs.co.kr|accessdate=January 12, 2019}}</ref> In 2016, she became an MC for an SM C&C web-variety program ''The Viewable SM'' together with [[Leeteuk]].<ref name=\"SMV\">{{cite news|url=http://www.osen.co.kr/article/G1110412785|title=SM, \uc0ac\ub0b4 \ubc29\uc1a1 'The \ubcf4\uc774\ub294 SM' \ub860\uce6d..\uccab \ud68c\ub294 \uc5d1\uc18c|language=ko|date=May 11, 2016|publisher=Osen|accessdate=January 12, 2019}}</ref> In December 2017, the singer Ragoon released his EP ''`s Talking'' which had its title track \"Story\" composed and co-penned by Yeri.<ref name=\"TSN1\">{{cite news|url=http://www.topstarnews.net/news/articleView.html?idxno=337769#08e1|title=[\uadfc\ud669] \ub808\ub4dc\ubca8\ubcb3(Red Velvet) \uc608\ub9ac, \uc774\uc81c\ub294 \uc791\uace1\uac00\ub85c? '\uc2dc\uc120\uc9d1\uc911'|language=ko|date=December 18, 2017|publisher=Top Star News|accessdate=January 12, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2018, Yeri was confirmed as part of the cast of [[JTBC]]'s new variety show ''Secret Unnie'' together with [[Han Chae-young]].<ref name=\"unnie\">{{cite news |title=[V Report] Black Pink Jennie, Jisoo accompanied by pets 'everywhere' |url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201808171355171738118_2 |accessdate=January 12, 2019 |work=The Korea Herald |date=August 17, 2018}}</ref> On December 13, 2018, Yeri, together with [[NCT (band)|NCT]]'s Renjun, Jeno and Jaemin took part in the third season of SM Entertainment's music project, ''SM Station''. The single's music video, the Korean version of \"Hair in the Air\", and the official Korean soundtrack of the television series ''[[Trolls: The Beat Goes On!]]'', were released on [[YouTube]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=311&aid=0000932922|title=[\uc96c\ud06c\ubc15\uc2a4] \uc608\ub9acXNCT, SM \ub0a8\ub9e4\ub4e4\uc774 \ub178\ub798\ud558\ub294 \ud589\ubcf5\uc774\ub780\u2026'Hair in the Air'|date=December 13, 2018|work=Naver|last1=|first1=|accessdate=January 12, 2019}}</ref> On March 14, 2019, the music video for Yeri's first self-composed solo project \"Dear Diary\" was released on YouTube as a part of ''SM Station Season 3''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thekrazemagazine.com/latest-updates/2019/3/18/red-velvets-yeri-gets-close-and-personal-with-dear-diary|title=Red Velvet's Yeri Gets Close and Personal with \"Dear Diary\"|website=The Kraze|language=en-US|access-date=2019-03-31}}</ref> In May, she was featured on South Korean rapper [[Giant Pink]]'s song \"Tuesday is better than Monday\".{{cn|date=March 2020}}\n\n==Personal life==\nYeri graduated from [[Hanlim Multi Art School]] in 2017.<ref>{{cite web |title=[BZ\ud3ec\ud1a0] \uc560\ud50c\ube44, \ud55c\ub9bc\uc608\uace0 \uc878\uc5c5\uc2dd \ucc38\uc11d |url=http://enter.etoday.co.kr/view/news_view.php?varAtcId=135444 |website=enter.etoday.co.kr |accessdate=January 12, 2019 |language=ko |date=February 9, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n{{see also|Red Velvet discography}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:14em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"1\" | Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Sales\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Gaon Chart|KOR]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/|title=Gaon Chart|publisher=Korea Music Content Industry Association}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL&targetTime=11&hitYear=2019&termGbn=week|title=Dear Diary \u2013 Week 11 of 2019|website=Gaon Chart|language=ko|accessdate=March 21, 2019}}\n</ref>\n|-\n! colspan=\"5\" |As lead artist\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|\"Dear Diary\" (\uc2a4\ubb3c\uc5d0\uac8c)\n\n| 2019\n| 200\n| {{N/A}}\n| ''[[SM Station|SM Station Season 3]]''\n|-\n! colspan=\"5\" |As featured artist\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|\"Tuesday Over Monday\" <br /> <small>(with [[Giant Pink]])</small>\n| 2019\n| \u2014\n| {{n/a}}\n| {{n/a|Non-album single}}\n|-\n\n! colspan=\"5\" |Collaborations\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|\"Hair in the Air\"<br /> <small>(with [[NCT (band)|NCT]]'s [[NCT (band)|Renjun]], [[NCT (band)|Jeno]], [[NCT (band)|Jaemin]])</small>\n| rowspan=\"1\"| 2018\n| \u2014\n| rowspan=\"2\" {{N/A}}\n| ''[[SM Station|SM Station Season 3]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|\"I Will Be Your Warmth\" ({{Korean|hangul=\ub108\uc758 \uc628\uae30\uac00 \ub418\uc5b4\uc904\uac8c|rr=Neoeui Ongiga Doeeojulge|labels=no}})<br />{{small|(with [[Babylon (singer)|Babylon]])}}\n| 2019\n| \u2014\n| {{N/A|Non-album single}}\n|-\n|colspan=\"5\" style=\"font-size:90%\"| \"\u2014\" denotes releases that did not chart or were not released in that region.\n|}\n\n=== Songwriting and composing credits ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Year\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Albu